The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                               IN THE CITY
                  
	Mohammedan Sporting and Mohun Bagan grounds have been certified fit to host the ensuing IFA Shield matches, after the PWD issued the required clearance. Meanwhile, a short-circuit caused a fire to break out in the Indian Football Association (IFA) office on Thursday evening. The fire started on the ground floor of the building on Sooterkin Street, which was closed off by an emergency crew. The staff was evacuated as two fire engines fought to the flames. No one was hurt.                
	 Come Sunday, the Bengal Table Tennis Association (BTTA), established in 1934, will organise a series of events to celebrate its platinum jubilee year.                                                                                                                                                                        
